<h1>Configuration System</h1>

<p>Plugs features a <strong>Zero-Config</strong> philosophy. By using "Smart Defaults" and internal auto-wiring, you can
    run a full-featured application with just a <code>.env</code> file.</p>

<h2 id="zero-config">1. Zero-Config & Smart Defaults</h2>

<p>The framework maintains internal defaults for all core components (Mail, Cache, Database, etc.) in
    <code>Plugs\Config\DefaultConfig</code>. You <strong>do not</strong> need to create files in <code>config/</code>
    unless you want deep customization.</p>

