<h2 id="auto-discovery">2. Auto-Discovery</h2>

<p>Plugs automatically discovers and registers your application's Service Providers.</p>

<ul>
    <li><strong>Location</strong>: All classes in <code>app/Providers/</code> are scanned and loaded automatically.</li>
    <li><strong>Customization</strong>: You no longer need to manually list providers in an <code>app.php</code> config
        file.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="deployment">3. Deployment Optimization</h2>

<p>For production, you can cache your configuration to eliminate filesystem hits:</p>

<pre><code># Compile defaults and .env into a single cache file
php theplugs optimize</code></pre>

<h2 id="overrides">4. Manual Overrides</h2>

<p>To override a default that isn't in <code>.env</code>, create a corresponding file in <code>config/</code>. The
    framework will <strong>recursively merge</strong> your settings into the defaults.</p>

<p><strong>Example: <code>config/mail.php</code></strong></p>
<pre><code>&lt;?php
return [
    'from' => [
        'address' => 'noreply@yourdomain.com',
        'name' => 'System'
    ]
];</code></pre>

<div class="alert alert-info">
    <i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> <strong>Note</strong>: You only need to return the keys you wish to change.
</div>
